Advansa, OMV Petrol Ofisi, Vestel Beyas: Turkey Stocks Preview

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-08-10T06:38:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/advansa-omv-petrol-ofisi-vestel-beyas-turkey-stocks-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 Index (XU100)  rose 677.71, or
1.3 percent, to 52,961.21 yesterday, snapping seven days of
losses.  Advansa Sasa Polyester Sanayi AS (SASA)  : The maker of
textiles and packaging materials said second-quarter net income
more than doubled to 16.9 million liras ($9.7 million),
according to a filing with the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  after
markets closed yesterday. The shares fell 4 kurus, or 2.3
percent, to 1.7 liras.  OMV  Petrol Ofisi (PTOFS)  AS: Turkey’s biggest fuel
retailer, which is owned by OMV AG, said losses in the second
quarter almost tripled to 27.5 million liras, according to a
statement to the exchange today. The shares dropped 2 kurus, or
0.5 percent, to 4.38 liras.  Vestel Beyaz Esya Sanayi & Ticaret AS (VESBE TI): The home
appliance maker reported second-quarter profit dropped to 9.3
million liras from 10.7 million liras a year earlier. The shares
were unchanged at 2.11 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
